{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XJ1LZF7TP4H2LYd2ugEeKf","type":"tool_result","content":"2-\n3-Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n4-workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n5:container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n6-results to a git branch.\n7-\n8-## Core Concepts\n9-\n10-- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n11:- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n12-- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n13-- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n14-- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n--\n42-\n43-### Step Configuration\n44-\n45:| Key | Type | Description |\n46-|-----|------|-------------|\n47-| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n48:| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n49-| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n50-| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n51-| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n--\n210-- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n211-- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n212-- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n213:- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n214-- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n215-\n216-## Prompt Assembly\n217-\n218-When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n219-\n220:1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n221-2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n222-3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n223-4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n--\n252-## Workflow Locations\n253-\n254-**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n255:via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n256-\n257-**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n258:Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n259-dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n260-execute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n261-fixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n--\n277-The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n278-object:\n279-\n280:| Field | Required | Description |\n281-|-------|----------|-------------|\n282-| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n283-| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n284-| `title` | no | Short summary |\n285:| `description` | no | Full description |\n286-| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n287-\n288-The daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n--\n296-```\n297-workflow \"list-tasks\" {\n298-  step fetch-tickets {\n299:    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n300-    results = [success, fail]\n301-  }\n302-\n--\n310-  }\n311-\n312-  step prepare-prompt {\n313:    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n314-    results = [success, fail]\n315-  }\n316-\n--\n327-\n328-workflow \"finalize\" {\n329-  step push-for-review {\n330:    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n331-    results = [success, fail]\n332-  }\n333-\n--\n336-}\n337-```\n338-\n339:The `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n340-receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n341-workflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n342-what cleanup to perform.\n343-\n344-### Host Step Environment Variables\n345-\n346:| Variable | Description |\n347-|----------|-------------|\n348-| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n349-| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n--\n355-\n356-### Container Environment Variables\n357-\n358:| Variable | Description |\n359-|----------|-------------|\n360-| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n361-| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n--\n381-  }\n382-\n383-  step quality {\n384:    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n385-    results = [success, fail]\n386-  }\n387-\n--\n428-cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n429-```\n430-\n431:| Flag | Default | Description |\n432-|------|---------|-------------|\n433-| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n434-| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n435-\n436-Creates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n437:host workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n438-\n439-### `cloche run`\n440-\n--\n444-cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n445-```\n446-\n447:| Flag | Description |\n448-|------|-------------|\n449-| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n450-| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n--\n473-### `cloche logs`\n474-\n475-```\n476:cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n477-```\n478-\n479:| Flag | Description |\n480-|------|-------------|\n481-| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n482:| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n483-| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n484-\n485-For active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n--\n533-│   │   ├── implement.md\n534-│   │   ├── fix.md\n535-│   │   └── update-docs.md\n536:│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n537-│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n538-│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n539-│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n540-│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n541-│       ├── output/\n542-│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n543:│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n544-│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n545-│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n546-│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n--\n550-\n551-## Daemon Configuration\n552-\n553:| Variable | Default | Description |\n554-|----------|---------|-------------|\n555-| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n556-| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n--\n565-\n566-### Client Configuration\n567-\n568:| Variable | Default | Description |\n569-|----------|---------|-------------|\n570-| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n571-| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"54672c45-4f78-41f5-b5cb-66398826bfb4","uuid":"0375e4a4-f35f-4e5d-b443-cfcf6b1365e3","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"2-\n3-Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n4-workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n5:container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n6-results to a git branch.\n7-\n8-## Core Concepts\n9-\n10-- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n11:- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n12-- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n13-- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n14-- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n--\n42-\n43-### Step Configuration\n44-\n45:| Key | Type | Description |\n46-|-----|------|-------------|\n47-| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n48:| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n49-| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n50-| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n51-| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n--\n210-- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are print